41static const char kFailedDueToIdentityFailed[] =
42 " failed because DTLS identity request failed";
43static const char kFailedDueToSessionShutdown[] =
44 " failed because the session was shut down";
45
46static const uint64_t kInitSessionVersion = 2;
47
48// Check that each sender has a unique ID.
49static bool ValidMediaSessionOptions(
50 const cricket::MediaSessionOptions& session_options) {
51 std::vector<cricket::SenderOptions> sorted_senders;
52 for (const cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options :
53 session_options.media_description_options) {
54 sorted_senders.insert(sorted_senders.end(),
55 media_description_options.sender_options.begin(),
56 media_description_options.sender_options.end());
57 }
58 absl::c_sort(sorted_senders, [](const cricket::SenderOptions& sender1,
59 const cricket::SenderOptions& sender2) {
60 return sender1.track_id < sender2.track_id;
61 });
62 return absl::c_adjacent_find(sorted_senders,
63 [](const cricket::SenderOptions& sender1,
64 const cricket::SenderOptions& sender2) {
65 return sender1.track_id == sender2.track_id;
66 }) == sorted_senders.end();
67}
68
69enum {
70 MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_SUCCESS,
71 MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_FAILED,
72 MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE
73};
74
75struct CreateSessionDescriptionMsg : public rtc::MessageData {
76 explicit CreateSessionDescriptionMsg(
77 webrtc::CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
78 RTCError error_in)
79 : observer(observer), error(std::move(error_in)) {}
80
81 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::CreateSessionDescriptionObserver> observer;
82 RTCError error;
83 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::SessionDescriptionInterface> description;
84};
85} // namespace

87void WebRtcCertificateGeneratorCallback::OnFailure() {
88 SignalRequestFailed();
89}
90
91void WebRtcCertificateGeneratorCallback::OnSuccess(
92 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) {
93 SignalCertificateReady(certificate);
94}
95
96// static
97void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::CopyCandidatesFromSessionDescription(
98 const SessionDescriptionInterface* source_desc,
99 const std::string& content_name,
100 SessionDescriptionInterface* dest_desc) {
101 if (!source_desc) {
102 return;
103 }
104 const cricket::ContentInfos& contents =
105 source_desc->description()->contents();
106 const cricket::ContentInfo* cinfo =
107 source_desc->description()->GetContentByName(content_name);
108 if (!cinfo) {
109 return;
110 }
111 size_t mediasection_index = static_cast<int>(cinfo - &contents[0]);
112 const IceCandidateCollection* source_candidates =
113 source_desc->candidates(mediasection_index);
114 const IceCandidateCollection* dest_candidates =
115 dest_desc->candidates(mediasection_index);
116 if (!source_candidates || !dest_candidates) {
117 return;
118 }
119 for (size_t n = 0; n < source_candidates->count(); ++n) {
120 const IceCandidateInterface* new_candidate = source_candidates->at(n);
121 if (!dest_candidates->HasCandidate(new_candidate)) {
122 dest_desc->AddCandidate(source_candidates->at(n));
123 }
124 }
125}

127WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory(
128 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
129 cricket::ChannelManager* channel_manager,
130 const SdpStateProvider* sdp_info,
131 const std::string& session_id,
132 bool dtls_enabled,
133 std::unique_ptr<rtc::RTCCertificateGeneratorInterface> cert_generator,
134 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate,
135 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
136 std::function<void(const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>&)>
137 on_certificate_ready)
138 : signaling_thread_(signaling_thread),
139 session_desc_factory_(channel_manager,
140 &transport_desc_factory_,
141 ssrc_generator),
142 // RFC 4566 suggested a Network Time Protocol (NTP) format timestamp
143 // as the session id and session version. To simplify, it should be fine
144 // to just use a random number as session id and start version from
145 // |kInitSessionVersion|.
146 session_version_(kInitSessionVersion),
147 cert_generator_(dtls_enabled ? std::move(cert_generator) : nullptr),
148 sdp_info_(sdp_info),
149 session_id_(session_id),
150 certificate_request_state_(CERTIFICATE_NOT_NEEDED),
151 on_certificate_ready_(on_certificate_ready) {
152 RTC_DCHECK(signaling_thread_);
153
154 if (!dtls_enabled) {
155 SetSdesPolicy(cricket::SEC_REQUIRED);
156 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "DTLS-SRTP disabled.";
157 return;
158 }
159
160 // SRTP-SDES is disabled if DTLS is on.
161 SetSdesPolicy(cricket::SEC_DISABLED);
162 if (certificate) {
163 // Use |certificate|.
164 certificate_request_state_ = CERTIFICATE_WAITING;
165
166 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "DTLS-SRTP enabled; has certificate parameter.";
167 // We already have a certificate but we wait to do |SetIdentity|; if we do
168 // it in the constructor then the caller has not had a chance to connect to
169 // |SignalCertificateReady|.
170 signaling_thread_->Post(
171 RTC_FROM_HERE, this, MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE,
172 new rtc::ScopedRefMessageData<rtc::RTCCertificate>(certificate));
173 } else {
174 // Generate certificate.
175 certificate_request_state_ = CERTIFICATE_WAITING;
176
177 auto callback = rtc::make_ref_counted<WebRtcCertificateGeneratorCallback>();
178 callback->SignalRequestFailed.connect(
179 this, &WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::OnCertificateRequestFailed);
180 callback->SignalCertificateReady.connect(
181 this, &WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::SetCertificate);
182
183 rtc::KeyParams key_params = rtc::KeyParams();
184 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
185 << "DTLS-SRTP enabled; sending DTLS identity request (key type: "
186 << key_params.type() << ").";
187
188 // Request certificate. This happens asynchronously, so that the caller gets
189 // a chance to connect to |SignalCertificateReady|.
190 cert_generator_->GenerateCertificateAsync(key_params, absl::nullopt,
191 callback);
192 }
193}
194
195WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::~WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory() {
196 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
197
198 // Fail any requests that were asked for before identity generation completed.
199 FailPendingRequests(kFailedDueToSessionShutdown);
200
201 // Process all pending notifications in the message queue. If we don't do
202 // this, requests will linger and not know they succeeded or failed.
203 rtc::MessageList list;
204 signaling_thread_->Clear(this, rtc::MQID_ANY, &list);
205 for (auto& msg : list) {
206 if (msg.message_id != MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE) {
207 OnMessage(&msg);
208 } else {
209 // Skip MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE because we don't want to trigger
210 // SetIdentity-related callbacks in the destructor. This can be a problem
211 // when WebRtcSession listens to the callback but it was the WebRtcSession
212 // destructor that caused WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory's destruction.
213 // The callback is then ignored, leaking memory allocated by OnMessage for
214 // MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE.
215 delete msg.pdata;
216 }
217 }
218}
219
220void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::CreateOffer(
221 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
222 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCOfferAnswerOptions& options,
223 const cricket::MediaSessionOptions& session_options) {
224 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
225 std::string error = "CreateOffer";
226 if (certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_FAILED) {
227 error += kFailedDueToIdentityFailed;
228 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
229 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
230 return;
231 }
232
233 if (!ValidMediaSessionOptions(session_options)) {
234 error += " called with invalid session options";
235 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
236 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
237 return;
238 }
239
240 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest request(
241 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest::kOffer, observer, session_options);
242 if (certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_WAITING) {
243 create_session_description_requests_.push(request);
244 } else {
245 RTC_DCHECK(certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_SUCCEEDED ||
246 certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_NOT_NEEDED);
247 InternalCreateOffer(request);
248 }
249}
250
251void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::CreateAnswer(
252 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
253 const cricket::MediaSessionOptions& session_options) {
254 std::string error = "CreateAnswer";
255 if (certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_FAILED) {
256 error += kFailedDueToIdentityFailed;
257 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
258 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
259 return;
260 }
261 if (!sdp_info_->remote_description()) {
262 error += " can't be called before SetRemoteDescription.";
263 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
264 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
265 return;
266 }
267 if (sdp_info_->remote_description()->GetType() != SdpType::kOffer) {
268 error += " failed because remote_description is not an offer.";
269 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
270 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
271 return;
272 }
273
274 if (!ValidMediaSessionOptions(session_options)) {
275 error += " called with invalid session options.";
276 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << error;
277 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(observer, error);
278 return;
279 }
280
281 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest request(
282 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest::kAnswer, observer, session_options);
283 if (certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_WAITING) {
284 create_session_description_requests_.push(request);
285 } else {
286 RTC_DCHECK(certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_SUCCEEDED ||
287 certificate_request_state_ == CERTIFICATE_NOT_NEEDED);
288 InternalCreateAnswer(request);
289 }
290}
291
292void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::SetSdesPolicy(
293 cricket::SecurePolicy secure_policy) {
294 session_desc_factory_.set_secure(secure_policy);
295}
296
297cricket::SecurePolicy WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::SdesPolicy() const {
298 return session_desc_factory_.secure();
299}
300
301void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::OnMessage(rtc::Message* msg) {
302 switch (msg->message_id) {
303 case MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_SUCCESS: {
304 CreateSessionDescriptionMsg* param =
305 static_cast<CreateSessionDescriptionMsg*>(msg->pdata);
306 param->observer->OnSuccess(param->description.release());
307 delete param;
308 break;
309 }
310 case MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_FAILED: {
311 CreateSessionDescriptionMsg* param =
312 static_cast<CreateSessionDescriptionMsg*>(msg->pdata);
313 param->observer->OnFailure(std::move(param->error));
314 delete param;
315 break;
316 }
317 case MSG_USE_CONSTRUCTOR_CERTIFICATE: {
318 rtc::ScopedRefMessageData<rtc::RTCCertificate>* param =
319 static_cast<rtc::ScopedRefMessageData<rtc::RTCCertificate>*>(
320 msg->pdata);
321 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Using certificate supplied to the constructor.";
322 SetCertificate(param->data());
323 delete param;
324 break;
325 }
326 default:
327 RTC_NOTREACHED();
328 break;
329 }
330}
331
332void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::InternalCreateOffer(
333 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest request) {
334 if (sdp_info_->local_description()) {
335 // If the needs-ice-restart flag is set as described by JSEP, we should
336 // generate an offer with a new ufrag/password to trigger an ICE restart.
337 for (cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions& options :
338 request.options.media_description_options) {
339 if (sdp_info_->NeedsIceRestart(options.mid)) {
340 options.transport_options.ice_restart = true;
341 }
342 }
343 }
344
345 std::unique_ptr<cricket::SessionDescription> desc =
346 session_desc_factory_.CreateOffer(
347 request.options, sdp_info_->local_description()
348 ? sdp_info_->local_description()->description()
349 : nullptr);
350 if (!desc) {
351 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(request.observer,
352 "Failed to initialize the offer.");
353 return;
354 }
355
356 // RFC 3264
357 // When issuing an offer that modifies the session,
358 // the "o=" line of the new SDP MUST be identical to that in the
359 // previous SDP, except that the version in the origin field MUST
360 // increment by one from the previous SDP.
361
362 // Just increase the version number by one each time when a new offer
363 // is created regardless if it's identical to the previous one or not.
364 // The |session_version_| is a uint64_t, the wrap around should not happen.
365 RTC_DCHECK(session_version_ + 1 > session_version_);
366 auto offer = std::make_unique<JsepSessionDescription>(
367 SdpType::kOffer, std::move(desc), session_id_,
368 rtc::ToString(session_version_++));
369 if (sdp_info_->local_description()) {
370 for (const cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions& options :
371 request.options.media_description_options) {
372 if (!options.transport_options.ice_restart) {
373 CopyCandidatesFromSessionDescription(sdp_info_->local_description(),
374 options.mid, offer.get());
375 }
376 }
377 }
378 PostCreateSessionDescriptionSucceeded(request.observer, std::move(offer));
379}
380
381void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::InternalCreateAnswer(
382 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest request) {
383 if (sdp_info_->remote_description()) {
384 for (cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions& options :
385 request.options.media_description_options) {
386 // According to http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5245#section-9.2.1.1
387 // an answer should also contain new ICE ufrag and password if an offer
388 // has been received with new ufrag and password.
389 options.transport_options.ice_restart =
390 sdp_info_->IceRestartPending(options.mid);
391 // We should pass the current DTLS role to the transport description
392 // factory, if there is already an existing ongoing session.
393 absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole> dtls_role =
394 sdp_info_->GetDtlsRole(options.mid);
395 if (dtls_role) {
396 options.transport_options.prefer_passive_role =
397 (rtc::SSL_SERVER == *dtls_role);
398 }
399 }
400 }
401
402 std::unique_ptr<cricket::SessionDescription> desc =
403 session_desc_factory_.CreateAnswer(
404 sdp_info_->remote_description()
405 ? sdp_info_->remote_description()->description()
406 : nullptr,
407 request.options,
408 sdp_info_->local_description()
409 ? sdp_info_->local_description()->description()
410 : nullptr);
411 if (!desc) {
412 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(request.observer,
413 "Failed to initialize the answer.");
414 return;
415 }
416
417 // RFC 3264
418 // If the answer is different from the offer in any way (different IP
419 // addresses, ports, etc.), the origin line MUST be different in the answer.
420 // In that case, the version number in the "o=" line of the answer is
421 // unrelated to the version number in the o line of the offer.
422 // Get a new version number by increasing the |session_version_answer_|.
423 // The |session_version_| is a uint64_t, the wrap around should not happen.
424 RTC_DCHECK(session_version_ + 1 > session_version_);
425 auto answer = std::make_unique<JsepSessionDescription>(
426 SdpType::kAnswer, std::move(desc), session_id_,
427 rtc::ToString(session_version_++));
428 if (sdp_info_->local_description()) {
429 // Include all local ICE candidates in the SessionDescription unless
430 // the remote peer has requested an ICE restart.
431 for (const cricket::MediaDescriptionOptions& options :
432 request.options.media_description_options) {
433 if (!options.transport_options.ice_restart) {
434 CopyCandidatesFromSessionDescription(sdp_info_->local_description(),
435 options.mid, answer.get());
436 }
437 }
438 }
439 PostCreateSessionDescriptionSucceeded(request.observer, std::move(answer));
440}
441
442void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::FailPendingRequests(
443 const std::string& reason) {
444 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
445 while (!create_session_description_requests_.empty()) {
446 const CreateSessionDescriptionRequest& request =
447 create_session_description_requests_.front();
448 PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(
449 request.observer,
450 ((request.type == CreateSessionDescriptionRequest::kOffer)
451 ? "CreateOffer"
452 : "CreateAnswer") +
453 reason);
454 create_session_description_requests_.pop();
455 }
456}
457
458void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::PostCreateSessionDescriptionFailed(
459 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
460 const std::string& error) {
461 CreateSessionDescriptionMsg* msg = new CreateSessionDescriptionMsg(
462 observer, RTCError(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR, std::string(error)));
463 signaling_thread_->Post(RTC_FROM_HERE, this,
464 MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_FAILED, msg);
465 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Create SDP failed: " << error;
466}
467
468void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::PostCreateSessionDescriptionSucceeded(
469 CreateSessionDescriptionObserver* observer,
470 std::unique_ptr<SessionDescriptionInterface> description) {
471 CreateSessionDescriptionMsg* msg =
472 new CreateSessionDescriptionMsg(observer, RTCError::OK());
473 msg->description = std::move(description);
474 signaling_thread_->Post(RTC_FROM_HERE, this,
475 MSG_CREATE_SESSIONDESCRIPTION_SUCCESS, msg);
476}
477
478void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::OnCertificateRequestFailed() {
479 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
480
481 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Asynchronous certificate generation request failed.";
482 certificate_request_state_ = CERTIFICATE_FAILED;
483
484 FailPendingRequests(kFailedDueToIdentityFailed);
485}
486
487void WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::SetCertificate(
488 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) {
489 RTC_DCHECK(certificate);
490 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Setting new certificate.";
491
492 certificate_request_state_ = CERTIFICATE_SUCCEEDED;
493
494 on_certificate_ready_(certificate);
495
496 transport_desc_factory_.set_certificate(certificate);
497 transport_desc_factory_.set_secure(cricket::SEC_ENABLED);
498
499 while (!create_session_description_requests_.empty()) {
500 if (create_session_description_requests_.front().type ==
501 CreateSessionDescriptionRequest::kOffer) {
502 InternalCreateOffer(create_session_description_requests_.front());
503 } else {
504 InternalCreateAnswer(create_session_description_requests_.front());
505 }
506 create_session_description_requests_.pop();
507 }
